#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/efficiency.md:1
msgid "Efficiency"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/efficiency.md:3
msgid "Avoid O(n) algorithms on hot paths (`no-linear-hot-paths`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/efficiency.md:5
msgid ""
"System call dispatch, scheduler enqueue, and frequent query operations must "
"not introduce O(n) complexity where n is a quantity that can be large "
"(number of processes, number of file descriptors, etc.). Demand sub-linear "
"alternatives."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/efficiency.md:13
msgid "// Bad — O(n) scan on every enqueue\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/efficiency.md:17
#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/efficiency.md:24
msgid "\"at least one CPU\""
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/efficiency.md:20
msgid ""
"// Good — maintain a priority queue\n"
"// so selection is O(log n)\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/efficiency.md:28
msgid ""
"See also: PR [\\#1790](https://github.com/asterinas/asterinas/pull/1790)."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/efficiency.md:31
msgid "Minimize unnecessary copies and allocations (`minimize-copies`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/efficiency.md:33
msgid ""
"Extra data copies — serializing to a stack buffer before writing, cloning an "
"`Arc` when a `&` reference suffices, collecting into a `Vec` when an "
"iterator would do — should be avoided."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/efficiency.md:40
msgid "// Bad — unnecessary Arc::clone\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/efficiency.md:45
msgid "// Good — borrow when ownership is not needed\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/efficiency.md:52
msgid ""
"See also: PR [\\#2582](https://github.com/asterinas/asterinas/pull/2582) and "
"[\\#2725](https://github.com/asterinas/asterinas/pull/2725)."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/efficiency.md:56
msgid ""
"No premature optimization without evidence (`no-premature-optimization`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/efficiency.md:58
msgid ""
"Performance optimizations must be justified with data. Introducing "
"complexity to solve a non-existent problem is rejected. If you claim a "
"change improves performance, show the numbers."
msgstr ""
